SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Maine Secretary of State’s Office ann
 ounces result of Senate District 30 recount
DESCRIPTION:AUGUSTA\, MAINE\n– The Department of the Secretary of State 
 announced the results for a recount for Maine Senate District 30 Democrat 
 (Gorham and part of Scarborough):\nWarren\, Sophia Bailey – 3\,838\nSato
 \, Eleanor Y. – 3\,807\nRepresentative Ellie Sato of Gorham requested a 
 recount after Representative Sophia Warren of Scarborough was declared the
  winner with a 29-vote margin. District 30 is currently represented by Sen
 ator Stacy Brenner\, who did not seek reelection.\nTwo additional recounts
 \, for House District 49 Republican and House District 135 Democrat\, are 
 scheduled for this Thursday. Recounts are open to the public and media and
  are livestreamed on the Secretary of State’s\nYouTube page\n.\nRecount 
 process:\nMaine statute\nTitle 21-A\, §737-A\nlays out a specific plan\, 
 process and any related costs for votes to be recounted. In a recount\, re
 presentatives of each candidate and staff members from the Department of t
 he Secretary of State manually review each paper ballot to determine the o
 fficial vote tally:\nIn non-Ranked Choice races:\nany candidate other than
  the apparent winner who desires a recount must file with the Secretary of
  State a written request for a recount within five business days after the
  election.\nIn Ranked Choice Voting races\n: only a candidate who received
  one of the top three rankings at the end of the penultimate round of rank
 ed‑choice counting may request a recount\, and they must file with the S
 ecretary of State a written request within five business days after result
 s are announced.\nOfficial results must be presented to the governor withi
 n 20 days of the election (Monday\, June 29) and will be posted on the\nEl
 ection Results page\n.\n###\nhttps://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretar
 y-states-office-announces-result-senate-district-30-recount
URL:https://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-states-office-announces
 -result-senate-district-30-recount
CATEGORIES:Maine Secretary of State
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
